1
00:00:01.256 --> 00:00:02.339
Crypto Agorism

2
00:00:03.062 --> 00:00:04.939
Free markets for a free world

3
00:00:06.611 --> 00:00:09.580
This presentation introduces Crypto Agorism

4
00:00:09.590 --> 00:00:10.714
what it is

5
00:00:10.716 --> 00:00:12.040
and how it helps people today

6
00:00:12.051 --> 00:00:14.174
to survive outside of the state

7
00:00:14.182 --> 00:00:17.501
and access services without
censorship or surveillance

8
00:00:17.894 --> 00:00:19.456
Important tools are

9
00:00:19.462 --> 00:00:20.609
cryptocurrencies

10
00:00:20.616 --> 00:00:21.715
anonymous services

11
00:00:21.717 --> 00:00:22.825
and gray markets

12
00:00:24.622 --> 00:00:26.890
Agorism means fair and free markets

13
00:00:26.892 --> 00:00:28.890
that operate outside of the state

14
00:00:29.391 --> 00:00:31.326
No company registration

15
00:00:31.328 --> 00:00:33.410
ID or permits are required

16
00:00:33.821 --> 00:00:36.274
Examples are under-the-table jobs

17
00:00:36.284 --> 00:00:38.038
informal apartment rentals

18
00:00:38.040 --> 00:00:39.556
and anonymous sim cards

19
00:00:40.349 --> 00:00:43.006
Cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin and Monero

20
00:00:43.008 --> 00:00:45.031
are good tools for agorist markets

21
00:00:45.587 --> 00:00:46.901
Unlike banking

22
00:00:46.903 --> 00:00:48.262
no government ID or

23
00:00:48.264 --> 00:00:50.393
corporate permission is required

24
00:00:50.863 --> 00:00:52.335
Just download a wallet

25
00:00:52.337 --> 00:00:55.159
and you can send and receive money worldwide

26
00:00:55.161 --> 00:00:56.152
without censorship

27
00:00:56.991 --> 00:00:59.093
Crypto Agorism unites agorists

28
00:00:59.095 --> 00:01:00.911
and cryptocurrency users

29
00:01:00.935 --> 00:01:02.659
to build practical free markets

30
00:01:03.842 --> 00:01:06.610
Agorism focuses on small businesses

31
00:01:06.612 --> 00:01:08.677
entrepreneurs and communities

32
00:01:08.679 --> 00:01:10.743
not state-backed corporations

33
00:01:11.669 --> 00:01:13.756
Small businesses are more flexible

34
00:01:13.758 --> 00:01:14.776
offer better

35
00:01:14.778 --> 00:01:16.852
more individualized service

36
00:01:16.854 --> 00:01:20.421
and have a closer relationship
between the buyer and seller

37
00:01:21.157 --> 00:01:23.131
Small businesses can also offer

38
00:01:23.149 --> 00:01:25.373
fairer pay and better working conditions

39
00:01:25.375 --> 00:01:27.820
due to direct deals with the producers

40
00:01:27.822 --> 00:01:29.452
and bypassing middlemen

41
00:01:29.454 --> 00:01:31.137
profiteers and CEOs

42
00:01:31.620 --> 00:01:34.962
An example is direct trade coffee vs. Nestle

43
00:01:36.531 --> 00:01:38.391
Agorism helps you to bypass

44
00:01:38.393 --> 00:01:40.123
the state's monopolies on money

45
00:01:40.125 --> 00:01:41.602
identity and markets

46
00:01:41.604 --> 00:01:44.608
which attempt to censor and surveil
the free market

47
00:01:45.433 --> 00:01:47.747
Fiat such as the US dollar

48
00:01:47.749 --> 00:01:49.659
is the state's monopoly on money

49
00:01:50.076 --> 00:01:52.701
The state can print more money limitlessly

50
00:01:52.703 --> 00:01:54.383
and manipulate the economy

51
00:01:55.029 --> 00:01:56.534
The state also forces

52
00:01:56.536 --> 00:01:58.772
government ID requirements onto banks

53
00:01:58.774 --> 00:02:01.659
which excludes millions of people without ID

54
00:02:01.661 --> 00:02:04.594
and surveils the financial transactions
of everyone else

55
00:02:05.370 --> 00:02:07.268
As the state is phasing out cash

56
00:02:07.270 --> 00:02:10.969
and planning to introduce
gatekept and surveilled CBDCs

57
00:02:10.971 --> 00:02:12.989
a free currency is necessary

58
00:02:14.149 --> 00:02:16.072
Cryptocurrencies are the answer

59
00:02:16.564 --> 00:02:18.817
Crypto operates outside of the state

60
00:02:19.297 --> 00:02:20.310
No country

61
00:02:20.312 --> 00:02:22.079
corporation or individual

62
00:02:22.081 --> 00:02:23.903
controls the network or issuance

63
00:02:24.797 --> 00:02:26.273
No government ID

64
00:02:26.275 --> 00:02:28.118
or application is required

65
00:02:28.711 --> 00:02:30.402
Simply download a wallet

66
00:02:30.404 --> 00:02:32.078
and you are ready to earn

67
00:02:32.080 --> 00:02:34.353
spend and save money worldwide

68
00:02:35.027 --> 00:02:37.527
Crypto transactions are pseudonymous

69
00:02:37.529 --> 00:02:39.127
censorship-resistant

70
00:02:39.129 --> 00:02:40.830
fast and have low fees

71
00:02:41.620 --> 00:02:43.269
This makes crypto perfect for

72
00:02:43.283 --> 00:02:44.623
online shopping

73
00:02:44.630 --> 00:02:45.969
money transfers

74
00:02:45.971 --> 00:02:47.016
fundraising

75
00:02:47.018 --> 00:02:48.518
and brick-and-mortar stores

76
00:02:48.957 --> 00:02:50.566
Additionally you can withdraw

77
00:02:50.568 --> 00:02:52.274
crypto to physical cash

78
00:02:52.276 --> 00:02:53.971
gift cards or gold

79
00:02:54.778 --> 00:02:58.018
The tyranny of digital ID already exists

80
00:02:58.020 --> 00:03:00.498
due to the state's monopoly on identity

81
00:03:01.202 --> 00:03:04.064
The state already refuses
to print passports

82
00:03:04.066 --> 00:03:06.763
national ID cards and birth certificates

83
00:03:06.765 --> 00:03:09.519
for approximately
1 billion people worldwide

84
00:03:10.246 --> 00:03:13.377
As more and more services
require government ID

85
00:03:13.379 --> 00:03:15.410
this shuts people out from necessities

86
00:03:15.412 --> 00:03:16.319
like jobs

87
00:03:16.321 --> 00:03:17.285
apartments

88
00:03:17.287 --> 00:03:18.334
healthcare

89
00:03:18.336 --> 00:03:19.114
mail

90
00:03:19.116 --> 00:03:20.623
sim cards and more

91
00:03:21.476 --> 00:03:23.549
Sadly there are no alternatives

92
00:03:24.192 --> 00:03:26.666
Flag Theory requires an existing ID

93
00:03:26.668 --> 00:03:28.737
Red Cross doesn't print IDs

94
00:03:28.739 --> 00:03:31.117
and non-government IDs aren't accepted

95
00:03:31.503 --> 00:03:32.956
If someone for example

96
00:03:32.958 --> 00:03:34.540
wasn't registered at birth

97
00:03:34.542 --> 00:03:36.811
there is no way for them to appeal

98
00:03:36.813 --> 00:03:39.053
or access ID in another way

99
00:03:40.282 --> 00:03:42.336
Government ID requirements

100
00:03:42.338 --> 00:03:44.385
also known as KYC

101
00:03:44.387 --> 00:03:46.489
have been excluding innocent people

102
00:03:46.491 --> 00:03:47.151
from jobs

103
00:03:47.153 --> 00:03:48.077
housing

104
00:03:48.079 --> 00:03:50.274
healthcare and more since decades

105
00:03:51.029 --> 00:03:53.385
Not only people who can't get ID

106
00:03:53.387 --> 00:03:55.409
but also people who need pseudonymity

107
00:03:55.411 --> 00:03:56.813
for safety reasons

108
00:03:56.815 --> 00:03:59.386
such as activists and victims of abuse

109
00:04:00.199 --> 00:04:02.663
This artificial barrier to the economy

110
00:04:02.665 --> 00:04:05.747
is cruel, fatalistic and
puts people in danger

111
00:04:06.177 --> 00:04:07.952
No third party should be able to

112
00:04:07.954 --> 00:04:10.151
universally censor an individual

113
00:04:10.153 --> 00:04:11.316
from the entire market

114
00:04:12.299 --> 00:04:13.353
For example

115
00:04:13.355 --> 00:04:15.702
if an employer likes
an applicant's skills

116
00:04:15.704 --> 00:04:16.587
and work ethic

117
00:04:16.589 --> 00:04:19.021
they should be able to hire this person

118
00:04:19.404 --> 00:04:20.306
In reality

119
00:04:20.308 --> 00:04:22.194
government ID requirements

120
00:04:22.196 --> 00:04:23.345
prevent this applicant

121
00:04:23.347 --> 00:04:24.916
from finding work anywhere

122
00:04:24.918 --> 00:04:26.961
despite their abilities and efforts

123
00:04:27.612 --> 00:04:28.417
Likewise

124
00:04:28.419 --> 00:04:29.762
if someone is ill

125
00:04:29.764 --> 00:04:30.755
goes to the doctor

126
00:04:30.757 --> 00:04:32.126
and can pay in cash

127
00:04:32.128 --> 00:04:34.667
they may be wrongly
refused treatment

128
00:04:34.669 --> 00:04:36.271
due to no government ID

129
00:04:36.441 --> 00:04:37.675
In a free market

130
00:04:37.677 --> 00:04:40.953
transactions are between
the buyer and seller only

131
00:04:40.955 --> 00:04:43.129
Trades are made on the basis of

132
00:04:43.131 --> 00:04:44.369
supply and demand

133
00:04:44.371 --> 00:04:47.067
without censorship from
external gatekeepers

134
00:04:47.788 --> 00:04:50.514
Government ID requirements
are unethical

135
00:04:50.516 --> 00:04:51.975
especially as the state refuses

136
00:04:51.977 --> 00:04:54.509
to print ID for millions of people

137
00:04:54.923 --> 00:04:56.002
In comparison

138
00:04:56.004 --> 00:04:58.287
agorism doesn't require ID

139
00:04:58.289 --> 00:04:59.939
and is open to everyone

140
00:05:01.413 --> 00:05:03.686
Agorist KYC-free services

141
00:05:03.688 --> 00:05:05.674
don't require government ID

142
00:05:05.676 --> 00:05:06.877
or state permission

143
00:05:07.280 --> 00:05:10.031
This provides equal and
meritocratic access

144
00:05:10.033 --> 00:05:10.912
to services

145
00:05:10.914 --> 00:05:12.316
preserves privacy

146
00:05:12.318 --> 00:05:14.863
and avoids state surveillance
and censorship

147
00:05:15.775 --> 00:05:16.830
Some examples are

148
00:05:16.832 --> 00:05:18.101
under-the-table jobs

149
00:05:18.103 --> 00:05:20.059
informal apartment rentals

150
00:05:20.061 --> 00:05:21.573
and anonymous health clinics

151
00:05:22.528 --> 00:05:24.410
Cryptocurrencies help people to

152
00:05:24.412 --> 00:05:25.791
earn money remotely

153
00:05:25.793 --> 00:05:26.870
shop online

154
00:05:26.872 --> 00:05:29.028
and send international
money transfers

155
00:05:29.688 --> 00:05:32.421
Anonymous sim cards
and PO boxes

156
00:05:32.423 --> 00:05:34.499
help people to access the internet

157
00:05:34.501 --> 00:05:36.418
and receive mail without ID

158
00:05:37.102 --> 00:05:39.500
Proxy merchants are also useful

159
00:05:39.502 --> 00:05:42.468
Some examples of
proxy services include

