A business registers sim cards

166
00:05:55.824 --> 00:05:57.237
under their company name

167
00:05:57.239 --> 00:05:58.971
and resells them anonymously

168
00:06:01.574 --> 00:06:03.979
There are many ways
to establish trust

169
00:06:03.981 --> 00:06:04.922
or authorization

170
00:06:04.924 --> 00:06:06.567
without government ID

171
00:06:06.569 --> 00:06:09.406
many of which are
successfully used today

172
00:06:10.109 --> 00:06:12.787
Many transactions can be
done anonymously

173
00:06:12.789 --> 00:06:13.802
for example

174
00:06:13.804 --> 00:06:17.233
buying food, clothes or
electronics in a store

175
00:06:17.620 --> 00:06:19.712
You only need to hand over the cash

176
00:06:19.714 --> 00:06:21.405
and the product is yours

177
00:06:21.829 --> 00:06:23.352
No name required

178
00:06:24.142 --> 00:06:25.795
PINs and passwords can help

179
00:06:25.797 --> 00:06:26.986
with authorization

180
00:06:26.988 --> 00:06:28.485
One example is

181
00:06:28.487 --> 00:06:30.536
a password to login to a website

182
00:06:30.538 --> 00:06:33.186
or a PIN sent by SMS or email

183
00:06:33.188 --> 00:06:34.395
to pick up a package

184
00:06:34.612 --> 00:06:36.625
Cryptographic key pairs

185
00:06:36.627 --> 00:06:38.544
are used for critical applications

186
00:06:38.546 --> 00:06:41.271
such as PGP encryption and signing

187
00:06:41.273 --> 00:06:42.963
for secure communication

188
00:06:42.965 --> 00:06:44.785
and proving ownership of funds

189
00:06:44.787 --> 00:06:45.671
with Bitcoin

190
00:06:46.060 --> 00:06:48.054
A pseudonymous key pair is enough

191
00:06:48.056 --> 00:06:49.385
to prove your identity

192
00:06:49.387 --> 00:06:51.000
or send money worldwide

193
00:06:51.760 --> 00:06:53.660
Online shopping and remote work

194
00:06:53.662 --> 00:06:55.189
can benefit from escrows

195
00:06:55.191 --> 00:06:57.274
such as Bitcoin's multisig

196
00:06:57.706 --> 00:06:59.166
This enables refunds

197
00:06:59.168 --> 00:07:00.484
in the case of a scam

198
00:07:01.113 --> 00:07:02.755
Cash deposits for rentals

199
00:07:02.757 --> 00:07:05.030
can protect against
damages or theft

200
00:07:05.362 --> 00:07:07.231
Customer reviews can help you to

201
00:07:07.233 --> 00:07:09.204
find trusted products or businesses

202
00:07:09.771 --> 00:07:12.431
Vouches for example from friends

203
00:07:12.433 --> 00:07:14.001
colleagues or landlords

204
00:07:14.003 --> 00:07:15.584
and web of trust can help

205
00:07:15.586 --> 00:07:16.926
to trust individuals

206
00:07:17.689 --> 00:07:20.595
While personal IDs are
a dangerous concept

207
00:07:20.597 --> 00:07:23.744
non-government IDs
from NGOs or companies

208
00:07:23.746 --> 00:07:25.850
are easier to access than the gatekept

209
00:07:25.852 --> 00:07:28.948
single point of failure of
government ID systems

210
00:07:30.242 --> 00:07:32.691
Next to the state monopoly on money

211
00:07:32.693 --> 00:07:33.655
and identity

212
00:07:33.657 --> 00:07:35.315
is the monopoly on markets

213
00:07:36.237 --> 00:07:37.730
Via regulations

214
00:07:37.732 --> 00:07:39.965
the state censors what can be sold

215
00:07:39.967 --> 00:07:40.978
who can sell

216
00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:42.246
and for what price

217
00:07:42.854 --> 00:07:44.423
The state excludes entire

218
00:07:44.425 --> 00:07:45.174
categories of products

219
00:07:45.181 --> 00:07:46.734
and groups of sellers

220
00:07:46.736 --> 00:07:47.806
from the economy

221
00:07:47.808 --> 00:07:50.066
despite market demand
for these services

222
00:07:50.990 --> 00:07:53.373
State regulations harm many people

223
00:07:53.877 --> 00:07:55.139
They make it difficult

224
00:07:55.141 --> 00:07:56.386
to access medicine

225
00:07:56.388 --> 00:07:57.690
affordable housing

226
00:07:57.692 --> 00:07:59.157
or even find a job

227
00:08:00.039 --> 00:08:01.586
High taxes make it difficult

228
00:08:01.588 --> 00:08:03.963
for regular people to
afford food and rent

229
00:08:03.965 --> 00:08:06.326
while the state immorally
spends these funds

230
00:08:06.328 --> 00:08:08.884
on corporate bailouts
corruption and war

231
00:08:09.929 --> 00:08:11.071
In comparison

232
00:08:11.073 --> 00:08:13.897
unregulated markets
are open to everyone

233
00:08:13.899 --> 00:08:15.216
without restrictions

234
00:08:15.799 --> 00:08:16.909
These may be known as

235
00:08:16.911 --> 00:08:17.846
gray markets

236
00:08:17.848 --> 00:08:19.290
parallel economies

237
00:08:19.292 --> 00:08:20.883
circular economies

238
00:08:20.885 --> 00:08:21.969
or Second Realms

239
00:08:22.877 --> 00:08:23.765
Some examples are

240
00:08:23.767 --> 00:08:25.894
local cash-in-hand markets

241
00:08:25.896 --> 00:08:27.373
online classifieds

242
00:08:27.375 --> 00:08:28.527
and darknet markets

243
00:08:29.446 --> 00:08:31.877
Opsec and risk management
are important

244
00:08:31.879 --> 00:08:34.486
but gray markets have
operated successfully

245
00:08:34.488 --> 00:08:35.415
since decades

246
00:08:35.417 --> 00:08:37.528
even in authoritarian countries

247
00:08:37.530 --> 00:08:40.021
and provide customers with
what they need

248
00:08:40.023 --> 00:08:41.390
and are unable to get

249
00:08:41.392 --> 00:08:42.841
from gatekept state markets

250
00:08:44.304 --> 00:08:46.173
Many day-to-day necessities

251
00:08:46.175 --> 00:08:48.221
take place as market transactions

252
00:08:48.681 --> 00:08:50.753
When you earn money from your job

253
00:08:50.755 --> 00:08:52.203
pay rent for your apartment

254
00:08:52.205 --> 00:08:54.164
buy food in a grocery store

255
00:08:54.166 --> 00:08:56.060
and pay for a gym membership

256
00:08:56.062 --> 00:08:57.771
All these are market transactions

257
00:08:57.773 --> 00:08:59.449
between a buyer and a seller

258
00:09:00.131 --> 00:09:01.673
These market transactions

259
00:09:01.675 --> 00:09:03.093
take place in communities

260
00:09:03.095 --> 00:09:04.406
such as with colleagues

261
00:09:04.408 --> 00:09:05.421
neighbors

262
00:09:05.423 --> 00:09:06.821
regular customers

263
00:09:06.823 --> 00:09:09.091
friends or fellow fans
of your hobby

264
00:09:09.799 --> 00:09:13.093
Local, global and online
agorist communities

265
00:09:13.095 --> 00:09:14.650
can help buyers and sellers to

266
00:09:14.652 --> 00:09:16.188
meet each other and build

267
00:09:16.190 --> 00:09:18.537
a parallel economy
free from state control

268
00:09:19.290 --> 00:09:22.113
Agorism doesn't require
mainstream adoption

269
00:09:22.115 --> 00:09:24.506
or integration with the
statist white market

270
00:09:25.029 --> 00:09:27.105
If you have one agorist employer

271
00:09:27.107 --> 00:09:28.550
one agorist landlord

272
00:09:28.552 --> 00:09:30.939
and shop from one
agorist grocery store

273
00:09:30.941 --> 00:09:31.782
that's enough

274
00:09:32.225 --> 00:09:34.163
A network of like-minded people

275
00:09:34.165 --> 00:09:35.752
and a peer-to-peer free market

276
00:09:35.754 --> 00:09:36.842
can help people to find

277
00:09:36.844 --> 00:09:37.943
what they need

278
00:09:39.756 --> 00:09:41.601
There are many ways
to participate

279
00:09:41.603 --> 00:09:42.959
in agorist markets

280
00:09:43.852 --> 00:09:45.555
The Gray Man strategy

281
00:09:45.557 --> 00:09:47.007
is when a white market business

282
00:09:47.009 --> 00:09:49.299
sells agorist services
under-the-table

283
00:09:49.301 --> 00:09:50.572
to trusted customers

284
00:09:51.214 --> 00:09:52.252
For example

285
00:09:52.254 --> 00:09:54.016
a local phone repair store

286
00:09:54.018 --> 00:09:56.353
sells anonymous sim cards
on request

287
00:09:56.355 --> 00:09:58.189
or a hotel rents out rooms

288
00:09:58.191 --> 00:10:00.233
without ID to people in need

289
